        "title": "Run memory flush before preflight compaction",
        "body": "Fixes #84695.\n\n## Summary\n\n- run automatic memory flush before preflight compaction in `runReplyAgent`\n- keep visible memory-flush errors on the same pre-run return path before the main reply\n- add regression coverage proving memory flush is invoked before preflight compaction\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `runReplyAgent` must run the memory-flush phase before the preflight-compaction phase so durable memory has a chance to run before aggressive transcript reduction.\n- **Real environment tested:** PR head `ccadfb5cbf03bd5fc7352df49b1726afff1bfa8e`, worktree `/Users/andy/openclaw-84792`, local Node `v24.15.0`, diagnostics timeline enabled via `OPENCLAW_DIAGNOSTICS=1` and `OPENCLAW_DIAGNOSTICS_TIMELINE_PATH`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Rebased the PR onto current `upstream/main`, then ran the patched `runReplyAgent` path through the direct runtime test with diagnostics timeline enabled and filtered the emitted timeline for `reply.memory_flush` and `reply.preflight_compaction` spans.\n\n```sh\nOPENCLAW_DIAGNOSTICS=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_DIAGNOSTICS_TIMELINE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-84792-current-head-timeline.jsonl \\\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts -- \\\n  -t 'resolves direct reply runs before early helpers read config'\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal capture from the command above:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"head\": \"ccadfb5cbf03bd5fc7352df49b1726afff1bfa8e\",\n  \"timelinePath\": \"/tmp/openclaw-84792-current-head-timeline.jsonl\",\n  \"phaseStartOrder\": [\n    \"reply.memory_flush\",\n    \"reply.preflight_compaction\"\n  ],\n  \"relevantEvents\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.start\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.memory_flush\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-03T08:14:42.702Z\",\n      \"attributes\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai\",\n        \"hasSessionKey\": true,\n        \"isHeartbeat\": false,\n        \"queueMode\": \"interrupt\",\n        \"isActive\": false,\n        \"blockStreamingEnabled\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.end\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.memory_flush\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-03T08:14:42.702Z\",\n      \"durationMs\": 0.623,\n      \"attributes\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai\",\n        \"hasSessionKey\": true,\n        \"isHeartbeat\": false,\n        \"queueMode\": \"interrupt\",\n        \"isActive\": false,\n        \"blockStreamingEnabled\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.start\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.preflight_compaction\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-03T08:14:42.703Z\",\n      \"attributes\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai\",\n        \"hasSessionKey\": true,\n        \"isHeartbeat\": false,\n        \"queueMode\": \"interrupt\",\n        \"isActive\": false,\n        \"blockStreamingEnabled\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.error\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.preflight_compaction\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-03T08:14:42.703Z\",\n      \"durationMs\": 0.185,\n      \"attributes\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai\",\n        \"hasSessionKey\": true,\n        \"isHeartbeat\": false,\n        \"queueMode\": \"interrupt\",\n        \"isActive\": false,\n        \"blockStreamingEnabled\": false\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the diagnostics timeline for the current PR head starts `reply.memory_flush` before `reply.preflight_compaction`, proving the pre-run maintenance order is now flush first, then compaction.\n\nWhat was not tested: no external provider turn was executed; the proof intentionally stops at the preflight compaction sentinel after exercising the real `runReplyAgent` pre-run maintenance path.\n\n## Supplemental validation\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-state.test.ts\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\nTests  86 passed (86)\n\npnpm check:test-types\n# passed\n\npnpm lint\n# passed\n\npnpm run format:check -- src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts\n# All matched files use the correct format.\n\ngit diff --check\n# clean\n```\n",
